HEADWORD: Menstruous
<hw>Men"stru*ous</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>menstruus</ets>, fr. <ets>mensis</ets> month. Cf.
<er>Menstruum</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Having the monthly flow or
discharge; menstruating.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Of or pertaining to the monthly flow;
catamenial.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Menstruum</ent>⟦br⟧
